qas.question: After what war did the English receive New Amsterdam?
How many Lenape lived in the area in 1700?
What was the name of the island the English traded to the Dutch in return for New Amsterdam?
In 1700, the Lenape Native American population had dwindled to how many?
After which war did England gain New York in exchange for Run, an Indonesian island?

context: At the end of the <a0_0><a4_0>Second Anglo-Dutch War<a4_0/><a0_0/>, the English gained New Amsterdam (New York) in North America in exchange for Dutch control of <a2_0>Run<a2_0/>, an Indonesian island. Several intertribal wars among the Native Americans and some epidemics brought on by contact with the Europeans caused sizable population losses for the Lenape between the years 1660 and 1670. By 1700, the Lenape population had diminished to <a1_0><a3_0>200<a3_0/><a1_0/>.
